            "answer_text": "The answer is YES  Credit: Image Because even when we are on a plane and should have our phone in airplane mode, we still could connect to the WiFi that is provided from the airlines. Unfortunately, the WiFi craze hasn\u2019t reached its fullest potential yet and we can\u2019t wait for the day it\u2019s included (for free) in the flights of the future. Want to know which airlines offer inflight internet access? Here are a few lists: American Airlines=777-300ER, 787 Dreamliner and some 777-200 planesEgypt Air=On selected A330-300HongKong Airlines=All Airbus A330-200 aircraftGaruda Indonesia=B777-300ER and Airbus 330-200/300Singapore Airlines=Airbus A380, 350 and Boeing 777-300ER Hope it helps, OKportal Technology ",
